      "id": 5243,
      "name": "",
      "username": "Alex",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2022-01-24T07:11:49.778Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Ramp test frequency really depends on the user and where they are in their periodization and how they feel.  Our plans are very specific sequences and the ramp test in themselves are not adding much value to these sequences.</p>\n<p>That said If someone is just coming back from a long break or for a beginner more frequent tests (monthly) are probably a good idea but if you have been training very consistently for a while then it is less important how often (8-12 weeks?).</p>\n<p>We do want to give the option to add them in but it\u2019s up to you.  I like to do them when I feel like I am progressing. Generally the are best fit in the middle of the recovery week.</p>",
      "post_number": 2,
      "post_type": 1,
