      "created_at": "2022-01-24T13:24:47.683Z",
      "cooked": "<p>As a general rule of thumb, which suits most recreational cyclists and works well, I recommend doing a test at the beginning of the season, another in the middle and another shortly before the end. But as Alex said it all depends on the rider\u2019s experience and how he feels throughout the season. If you feel strong and you see that the training is being very easy, it may be time to take a test. If, on the contrary, they are being challenging enough, it would not be necessary.</p>",
